{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:sirach.14",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 14,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 14 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:1",
      "text": "Blessed is the man that hath not slipped by a word out of his mouth, and is not pricked with the remorse of sin.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:2",
      "text": "Happy is he that hath had no sadness of his mind, and who is not fallen from his hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:3",
      "text": "Riches are not comely for a covetous man and a niggard, and what should an envious man do with gold?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:4",
      "text": "He that gathereth together by wronging his own soul, gathereth for others, and another will squander away his goods in rioting.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:5",
      "text": "He that is evil to himself, to whom will he be good? and he shall not take pleasure in his goods.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:6",
      "text": "There is none worse than he that envieth himself, and this is the reward of his wickedness:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:7",
      "text": "And if he do good, he doth it ignorantly, and unwillingly: and at the last he discovereth his wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:8",
      "text": "The eye of the envious is wicked: and he turneth away his face, and despiseth his own soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:9",
      "text": "The eye of the covetous man is insatiable in his portion of iniquity: he will not be satisfied till he consume his own soul, drying it up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:10",
      "text": "An evil eye is towards evil things: and he shall not have his fill of bread, but shall be needy and pensive at his own table.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:11",
      "text": "My son, if thou have any thing, do good to thyself, and offer to God worthy offerings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:12",
      "text": "Remember that death is not slow, and that the covenant of hell hath been shewn to thee: for the covenant of this world shall surely die.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:13",
      "text": "Do good to thy friend before thou die, and according to thy ability, stretching out thy hand give to the poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:14",
      "text": "Defraud not thyself of the good day, and let not the part of a good gift overpass thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:15",
      "text": "Shalt thou not leave to others to divide by lot thy sorrows and labours?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:16",
      "text": "Give and take, and justify thy soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:17",
      "text": "Before thy death work justice: for in hell there is no finding food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:18",
      "text": "All flesh shall fade as grass, and as the leaf that springeth out on a green tree.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:19",
      "text": "Some grow, and some fall off: so is the generation of flesh and blood, one cometh to an end, and another is born.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:20",
      "text": "Every work that is corruptible shall fail in the end: and the worker thereof shall go with it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:21",
      "text": "And every excellent work shall be justified: and the worker thereof shall be honoured therein.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:22",
      "text": "Blessed is the man that shall continue in wisdom, and that shall meditate in his justice, and in his mind shall think of the all seeing eye of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:23",
      "text": "He that considereth her ways in his heart, and hath understanding in her secrets, who goeth after her as one that traceth, and stayeth in her ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:24",
      "text": "He who looketh in at her windows, and hearkeneth at her door.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:25",
      "text": "He that lodgeth near her house, and fastening a pin in her walls shall set up his tent high unto her, where good things shall rest in his lodging for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:26",
      "text": "He shall set his children under her shelter, and shall lodge under her branches:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:sirach.14.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:27",
      "text": "He shall be protected under her covering from the heat, and shall rest in her glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
